---| EDITORIAL |------------------| SOMETHING HAPPENED IN THE WAY TO HEAVEN |---
    ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯                    ¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
Hello and welcome to the 17th issue of AmiChannel News.

If you are a regular reader of AmiChannel News (the only one! ;-D) probably you
are wondering what happened to the December issue. Well, it has been "lost" due
to a Y2K bug ;-D. Not really, I have had problems with my ISP, so I could not
upload this issue in time and, as the title of this editorial suggests,
"something happened in the way to heaven".

In case you don't know by now, Amiga has been sold... again! Gateway was only
interested in the patents and nothing else, so they were looking to sold the
other parts they did not wanted. And the new owner of the Amiga is... AMINO.

Again, in case you don't know, Amino is the company that Fleecy Moss and Bill
McEwen founded back in September when the second was fired by Amiga, some days
before the Amiga fiasco. For more information about Amino, you can read
@{"this article" Link not43}.

But, what about the future?. Well probably you want to read
@{"this letter" Link not42} from Bill who explained it all. Well, almost all,
because a more detailed press released is expect very soon. Although it is not
oficial, the Amino's plan is more or less the same of the designed in times of
Amiga Inc. in Collas times. The only difference is that we are going to see
another player in Amiga. QNX is not the kernel selected by Amino, neither do
Linux.

Write this name and remember where you have first read: TAO Group. The name of
the kernel: Elate. I do not have a lot of information about this kernel, but I
expect to look into this and post into the SAUG-news site. So watch regularly
for updated information about the future, who promise very interesting.

Remember to visit the SAUG website, which is located in:

	http://teleline.terra.es/personal/angelsau/index.html

And if you want to contribute to this effort, you can send your articles to:

	noticias@saug.org

Thanks for reading and I hope you enjoy this issue.

===============================================================================
Angel Alvarez Díaz - noticias@saug.org
Editor of the e-magazine AmiChannel News
Responsible of the News Departament of S.A.U.G and Mundo Amiga
Member of C.U.A.E Nº 293 - FOREIGN DIRECTOR
