@node not16 "LAMBDA STATUS"

                                 LAMBDA STATUS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Lambda is a freelance project striving to create a high quality 3D space action
game with a compelling storyline. It is being developed totally
non-professionally by four men in their free time with no salary - just an urge
to make a dream come true.

Some of the most basic services of the new 3D engine have been defined and also
implemented in OpenGL. The engine is still nothing more than a fancy mouse
driven object viewer, but the code beneath the surface is slowly maturing. The
only really new features are colored lighting and reflection mapping, both of
which are readily provided by OpenGL. For the software rendering engine they
will of course have to be written from scratch. For the software renderer it is
probably wise to also offer an option for switching to monochromatic lighting,
which should be faster.

Work on the virtual machine has also finally been started, though many problems
still need to be solved and many questions answered. Some basic definitions have
been made, but due to technical vs. idealistic problems it may take a while
before I get started properly.

The news of Descent: Freespace coming to the Amiga was initially a punch in the
face. After all, one of the reasons we started developing Lambda was the lack of
modern 3D space action games for the Amiga. After the initial shock I decided
that we would still do our best and perhaps even beat Freespace. We do need to
try to move a little further away from the Freespace gameplay, though, to
prevent unwanted redundancy in the genre. Since the beginning of the project the
competition is now tougher than ever; something we should have anticipated. Now
we'll just have to work even harder.

More info at http://www.hut.fi/u/mkalline/lambda/index.html
