@node not23 "IMMORTAL CD HAS BEEN RELEASED"

                         IMMORTAL CD HAS BEEN RELEASED
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Immortal is a videogame soundtrack album with a special CD-Rom data section for
computer owners.

Videogame music began with a few clumsy beeps from the games in the early 80's,
but with the rapid evolution in computer technology, game tunes became major
studio productions and the videogame music style affirmed itself as a
respectable genre in the world of music. The Amiga computer was one of the first
machines featuring fantastic music in it's games. Some of this music has now
been revamped into studio quality in Immortal.

Immortal started to take shape in the mind of Amiga game music composer Ruben
Monteiro back in March 1997, with the idea of creating an Audio cd with studio
enhancements of classic Amiga game tunes. Since it would contain only music from
the Amiga computer's golden era of 1989-1993, it was to be called 'Roots',
refering that music as precisely the root of videogame music of nowadays.

As he progressed development, he started to notice the work of the recent Amiga
musicians. They sounded equally as exciting, and still not available in CDaudio
format, so he got in touch with musicians Jochen Heizmann, Darryl Sloan who were
to create studio mixes of their game music, and later Bjorn Lynne, who licensed
some of his game and album music for Immortal.

Later in 1998, Amiga game music legends Allister Brimble, probably the best
Amiga game composer ever, and Barry Leitch, one of the best musicians from the
Commodore64 computer scene and also Amiga, joined the Immortal productive team.

Immortal is one of the most featured and complete music albums ever. In there
you'll find the full soundtrack from the gameShadow of the Beast, additional
music fromDafel: Bloodline, Project X (new 99 version), Superfrog, BlockheadII,
The Strangers, The Final Odyssey, Harlequin, Utopia, Alien Breed 3D, Space
Station 3000, Gunbee F-99,  andTurrican (new special version of the level 5
music from the first chapter of the series).

On the computer data part, there's the Immortal videoclip.

More info at http://www.monteiro-music.com/immortal/.
