@node not28 "CLICKBOOM'S S-FILES - FILE 2: QUAKE PPC"

                    CLICKBOOM'S S-FILES - FILE 2: QUAKE PPC
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Just 2 days ago I told you guys that S-files would be a monthly thing, but
already we've got some hot news to share with you, so here is my second file
already.

I am happy to announce that the creator of Quake, id software's legendary John
Carmack, has released Quake sources on the Internet.

As you probably know, we had a lot of trouble with the PPC version of Quake --
first Amiga Inc. went the non-PPC way, then there was a big problem with piracy,
then an illegal PPC version of the code appeared on Aminet, etc. On top of that,
QuakeWorld was a non-commercial product on PC, so we couldn't create that
either.

Therefore, no matter how much we wanted to see Quake on PPC Amigas, we were
really stuck from the commercial point of view. Then, at the beginning of the
year we were told that John would release Quake sources, and we were releived,
because we knew that would open doors for legal PPC Quake code created by
talented Amiga programmers.

So, the wait is over, and we can finally put all the Quake PPC troubles behind
-- anyone on Amiga can compile and modify those sources to create a PPC Amiga
executable. Of course, there is more to it than just PPC -- Warp3D, QuakeWorld
and other interesting developments can and should happen, as well.

However, if you are going to be involved in any form of distribution of the
newly created executables please, please, please, READ AND OBEY THE GNU LICENCE.
Also, please note what John says:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"All of the Quake data files remain copyrighted and licensed under the original
terms, so you cannot redistribute data from the original game..."

Briefly, what this means is that you can create new Quake PPC, QuakeWorld and
other executables and spread THE CODE freely around, but you MAY NOT COPY QUAKE
LEVELS, TEXTURES, or other files found on the Quake CD.

Also, if you wish to use new Quake PPC executables YOU MUST OWN A COPY OF QUAKE.
To buy Quake, just go http://pxlcomputers.com/shopping.html.

So, the next step is to finally have a legal PPC version of Quake. If you are a
programmer and would like to work with Quake sources, download John's original
archive here. Then, let us know at info@clickboom.com that you want to work on
it, and we will help you and other Amiga programmers to cooperate, so that PPC
versions (as well as QuakeWorld) are top-notch. Also, that will help unnecessary
overlapping of work (ie. two guys working on the same part of the code).

And last, but certainly not least, we will post all of the Quake executables on
our web site for users to download. So, let's create "The New Tomorrow" Quake.

More info at http://clickboom.com/
